comment.body: holy shit thank you so goddamn much!!!
Wait so I'm confused, when you say "medical disorder" what do you mean; as well as what context was it in? I'm relatively new here, so sorry if this is common knowledge.

@Kaffie: Hmm, that's really fucked. My only guess is that it must of been a false positive. They were probably testing out new changes to the classifier that they use to catch violations of their ToS. 

Tbh the whole thing that these companies try to do with regulations seems to be so counter-productive. It seems to cause even more problems than originally. I just cannot see how they think doubling down on shit like this is going to fix their problems, but yeah, I agree fuck that shit.
thank you so much for starting work on this it really is a big problem!
